text: Rachel Anne McAdams (born November 17, 1978) is a Canadian actress. She was nominated for the Orange Rising Star Award in 2006. She is commonly known for her role as Regina George in Mean Girls. She was born in London, Ontario and grew up in St. Thomas, Ontario. She had major roles in The Hot Chick, Mean Girls, The Notebook, Wedding Crashers, Red Eye, The Family Stone, State of Play, The Time Traveler's Wife, Sherlock Holmes, Morning Glory, Midnight in Paris, The Vow About Time and Eurovision Song Contest: The Story of Fire Saga. ==References== == Other websites == * Category:Actors from London, Ontario Category:Canadian movie actors Category:Canadian television actors Category:1978 births Category:Living people Category:Actors from Toronto Category:Canadian stage actors Category:Canadian voice actors Category:Screen Actors Guild Award winners Category:York University alumni
